data-triple-N3.o: "* End of all conflict between Texas and Mexico"@en

"The MexicanAmerican War, also known as the Mexican War or the U.S. Mexican War, was an armed conflict between the United States of America and the United Mexican States from 1846 to 1848 in the wake of the 1845 U.S. annexation of Texas, which Mexico considered part of its territory despite the 1836 Texas Revolution. Combat operations lasted a year and a half, from spring 1846 to fall 1847."@en
